content: Finally, I've found this land. I can't wait to start exploring.
But... why has everything here lost its color?
Don't worry. I know how to get the colors back.
Look! The colors have returned.
Hmm? Look there, something is moving. Maybe we'll find something useful.
Let's go check it out!
Wow, it's gold! Collect it. Maybe we'll find it come in handy later.
I found something new. Let's go and check it out!
What is this place? Where's the monkey? Where has it gone?
Look, this is a relic.
I can only imagine how magnificent this building used to be.
Yet now... it's all wrecked.
Forget about the monkey. Let's do something to restore this relic.
Is that what you're thinking, too? This is amazing! Let's get working.
Oh, great!
Maybe that's why I always dreamed about Zealandia.
These relics... are beckoning me...
They want me to restore them to their former glory.

name: bubble_story_2
content: Hey, that monkey took my backpack!

name: bubble_story_2
content: We'll find that cursed monkey and get the backpack back.
It ran away. Let's hurry up and stop it!
And again, it has escaped.
We were so focused on that monkey that we seem to have lost our way.
I've no idea where we are now. And you?
Oh, don't worry , my friend.
There will always be surprises. That's what explorations are all about.
Cheer up, and we'll beat the odds.
Our compass is in the backpack. Get it back and we'll find our way.
That damned monkey! It will not escape me again. I swear.
That monkey is really a nuisance.
Oh! Yeah! Finally, our backpack is back. Let me see.
Oh, hey, we're already outside of the forest. And the sea is there.
That monkey seemed to be guiding us out of the forest. Don't you agree?
Well, I'm not really fond of that monkey, though I don't want to harm it, either.
What are we gonna do next? Hmm... we'll continue our journey, of course.
The islands, mountains and oceans... are awaiting us!

name: bubble_story_3
content: We set off from Minos Island and continued our journey.
On the second night, we encountered a storm.
Furious waves were bashing our ship, as if they would sink it any time.
However, misfortune might be a blessing in disguise.
If it wasn't for that storm, we wouldn't have found the amazing underwater world.
We survived the storm and made it to the wonderful underwater world.
This is amazing.
Have you noticed that? Everything under the sea has lost its color, too.
What exactly has happened?
Don't worry. We'll figure it out, right?
Do you feel that?
The ground is shaking. Some sort of huge animal is approaching us.
It's a turtle. It's coming at us.
Pull yourself together, we must beat it. I don't want to become its dinner.
Phew, that was close. We've overcome the turtle! You really should compliment me more.
Let's keep going.
I heard there are shipwrecks full of treasure at the bottom of the sea.
Hopefully, we'll find one.
That turtle just won't give up.
Well, then I guess our adventure will not go smoothly.
Danger keeps me sharp. That's not bad, if we look on the bright side.
Look, there's a big wreck. Judging by the extent of corrosion,
this big guy must have stayed here for at least a thousand years.
Shall we go inside? Well... that might be risky, but it's worth it.
Hey, I found a journal, maybe written by one of the crew.
You want to take a look?
Alright, the scribble is a bit illegible, but I'll try to make out of it.
Let's keep going while I'm reading it.
The journal reads, "On May 20th,
we set out from our homeland to the distant land of Zealandia, our ship laden with goods."
It seems to be a merchant ship from another continent.
Where do you think they came from? Asia, Europe? Or North America?
The captain shot an albatross, and that caused uneasiness among us.
Albatrosses are the messengers from the God of the Sea,
and killing them will provoke His anger."
That's what the journal says.
Have you ever heard of The Rime of the Ancient Mariner?
That poem is also about a sailor who shot an albatross and caused his doom.
Seafarers believe that albatrosses are a symbol of good luck.
But... we didn't shoot any albatross, but our ship sank anyway.
Let's move on. Now there is a shipwreck, there must be some treasure.
Maybe we'll find something amazing.
The last paragraph says,
"The captain shot the albatross and offended the God of the Sea.
Now the waves are raging. Our ship is doomed."
It seems they were also caught in a storm,
but now we know that it's a natural phenomenon and has nothing to do with gods or curses.
Oh, my Gosh! This ship is shaking. Something must be banging it.
This shipwreck has stayed here for too long time to withstand strong impacts.
Let's get out of here, just to be on the safe side.
So, it is this turtle who was ramming the ship. It almost got us killed.
It seems the animals in Zealandia have developed a habit of running away when they can't best their opponent.
Don't worry. Next time we'll get rid if it once and for all.
turtle or monkey, they are no rivals of me.
Wait a sec... I'm no stranger to such shaking..
Schools of fish are swimming away, as if they are running from something terrible.
I have a bad feeling about this. A submarine earthquake is about to happen! Run away!

name: bubble_story_4
content: We moved along the bottom of the sea but failed to escape from the whirlpool.
When I woke up again, I found myself on a beach. I had no idea where I was.
The only thing I knew for sure was that I was still on the land of Zealandia, alive.
After a long walk in a strange world, I finally reached this jungle.
A change of scenery, at last.
All these days we've been staying at the bottom of the sea, or on the beach. It really gives me a "seasick".
Phew... the nature smells great.
The jungle could be full of unexpected danger, especially savages!
Nobody lives here?
Now that you mention it, we haven't met anyone since we reached Zealandia.
Have the residents abandoned this land already?
It looks like we've arrived at a primitive clan.
There are a number of structures with a totem along the way. The totem must be their symbol.
If we're lucky, maybe we'll run into a bunch of hospitable aborigines.
And if we are not? Oh, you don't want to know.
Does this monkey look familiar to you?
Yeah, it's the one we met on Minos Island. Or maybe that monkey has a brother.

name: bubble_story_1
content: When I was a kid, I always dreamed of a new, undiscovered land.
As I grew up, I treaded mountains and crossed rivers, exploring all over the world.
Eventually, I found the promised land in my dream. It's Zealandia, the place where my dream began.
Look, I found something. It looks like a map.
This is a map of Zealandia.
Great, the map will guide us.
It will also tell us where the relics are.
Return and discover more!
Tap here to return to the relic scene and continue to repair it.
Be careful. There could be more tough animals along the way besides that monkey.
Ah, don’t be afraid, my friend.
That’s how explorations work.
Accidents happen. Be optimistic. We can overcome the challenges.
We’re completely lost and can’t find the monkey.
I wish grandfather were here. He’d never get lost in a forest.
My grandfather? Would you like to hear his story? I don’t know where to start.
Let me see.
My grandfather is a great explorer, who has been to many dangerous places.
He would always overcome the dangers and challenges.
But I haven’t seen him for around ten years.
He never came back after his last exploration.
GPS signals showed that the last place he appeared was in Oceania.
Right. It's right in this area.
I was thinking that maybe my grandfather was on this continent.
I thought about the possibility that he’s probably...
Ah, that makes me so sad. Let’s not talk about this anymore.
Look, it’s the monkey. Can we defeat it this time?
That sneaky monkey was a fast runner.
I feel like this monkey took away my backpack on purpose. What’s it after?
Maybe we should talk to the monkey next time we see it.
Hey, monkey. Do you want to sit down and talk?
What am I doing? How could a monkey understand my words?
I’ll give some thought to learning how to speak animalese.
I hate that monkey! I won’t let you run away next time. I swear.
It’s a turtle. It’s slamming the shipwreck. It nearly killed us.
I need to teach this turtle a lesson.
Undersea battle isn’t our strength. The turtle ran away again.
I hope it won’t come back with a group of turtles.
It’s waiting for us ahead. Think about this.
Maybe the monkey on Minos Island and the turtle in the sea
appeared in front of us on purpose.
Were they leading the way or guarding something?
Only we can find the answer to that question.
Maybe that answer could shed light on the sinking of Zealandia.
My grandfather spent his entire life searching for the truth.
If we share the same goal with him,
we’ll meet him again one day no matter how long has passed.
Do you know how long we’ve been walking undersea?
I don’t. But we should be able to get out soon, judging from how the landscape changes.
This turtle won't give up. It has followed us all the way.
We can get rid of the turtle once we leave the sea.
But I’m sure more animals would be waiting for us ahead on our way.
What’s next? An eagle? A gorilla? A snake?
A monkey! Does this monkey look familiar to you?
Yes, it’s like the one we ran into on Minos Island. Perhaps it has a brother.
It’s in our way. Looks like we’ll have to defeat it to move on.
It ran away. Maybe it went looking for its brother.
Look, we’re at a desert.
Looks like Zealandia has a variety of landscapes.
This was home to Zealandia Empire, the richest empire in its time.
It’s been long since Zealandia Empire fell and no one knows why it did.
Some people say it's because they angered their god.
Others say they went to an exoplanet. Which theory do you prefer?
Me? I prefer digging up the truth behind the fall of the empire myself over legends.
I can’t believe it. An eagle!
I told you. There would be a lot of tough animals on our way.
Let’s get moving and get rid of these tricky creatures!
Eagles rule the sky. But I rule explorations.
After all, I am an explorer by birth.
Didn’t I tell you before?
We have quite a few explorers in our family.
My father, my grandfather, my great grandfather... We are all explorers.
Perhaps we’re all on a mission for something.
I think my mission now is to defeat the eagle.
If I could, I’d love to ride the eagle and fly in the sky.
Oh no! A sand storm is coming. We need a shelter.
Wow ...... we have successfully repaired the ruins.Maybe there is a treasure in it.

name: bubble_story_5
content: As the sandstorm approached, I tried to find shelter before it arrived.
However, I didn't make it before the storm caught me.
Caught right in the sandstorm that darkened the sky, I couldn't tell where I was going, and my compass didn't work.
Suddenly, a light appeared in front of me on my left, and I followed its guidance.
In the end, I managed to make it here, a temple for the Goddess of Storm.
Weird, the sandstorm stops here. Is it because of the patroness in the temple?
If this is the case, I'm curious about this patroness.
Although this place is now in complete ruins, I believe it has seen better days.
Who exactly built this temple here?
Let's explore this place and see if we can find the answer.
I found fragments of some sort of statue, made of gold and ivory.
Whoever built this temple must have been very rich and pious.
Most of the objects in this temple are covered in sand.
They must have been buried beneath it.
Why did the builders of this temple abandon it?
Where did they go? Was its doom an act of the gods? Or a man-made disaster?
Hey, don't look at me like that. All explorers are curious and always have questions.
Here comes our trouble. That eagle has followed us here.
I thought it was consumed by the sandstorm.
How do you think the eagle found us? Because of its sharp sense of smell?
No, no. I don't have any bad smells on me. Perhaps it's because you stink.
I found a stone tablet with a long inscription,
though I could only make out a small part of it.
The inscription reads, "O, Ankhla, my great goddess.
Thank you for granting us this oasis and keeping us safe from sandstorms.
The people of the Senavia Kingdom will honor your grace for eternity!"
In short, there was an oasis in the desert, where a kingdom named "Senavia" was founded.
This temple was built by those folks.
I wonder if that oasis is still there. I'd love to go there and take a bath.
I'm literally covered in sand.
Although explorations are always fun,
it's a nuisance that I can't bathe whenever I want.
Seeing that eagle, I can't help but wonder maybe there's really an oasis in the desert,
otherwise how could that eagle survive?
Every living being needs water.
We might find the oasis by following that eagle.
There's nothing else useful here.
We'll have to find that oasis if we really want to figure out what happened to this temple.
Let's pack up and get out of here. Hopefully the sandstorm has stopped.
That eagle just won't give up. I don't want to see it again once we get out of the temple.
Let's deal with it once and for all.
Game over! So long, annoying eagle!
A map piece. Gather all of them to find the lost  relics. Click here to enter the map.
Click to view the pieces.
It looks like you need to collect more pieces. I can't wait to see the complete look of the relic!
Good job! You find the relic entrance. Maybe there are some treasures. Let's start our treasure hunt!
The wonderful moments of Chloe's adventure are here. Come to have a look!
